&lt;p&gt;HEREFORDSHIRE DENTAL ACCESS CENTRE&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Dental Access Centre is part of Wye Valley NHS Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It is located on the border of Wales and provides the gateway to the Brecon Beacons to the west and Malvern Hills and Worcestershire to the east.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;1 post based in Hereford&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Gaol Street Dental Access Centre &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Full time 37.5 hours per week &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Monday - Friday 8.30 – 5pm &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to an enthusiastic, self-motivated Dental Receptionist to work at the Dental Access Centres in Hereford. You will be expected to efficiently assist with the daily running of the reception for the Dental Service. Communication with patients, carers, face to face contact with patients and all visitors is key.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role will include all aspects of booking appointments, dealing with telephone and counter enquiries from patients, other health care professionals and other dentists. You will also undertake various clerical duties. The successful candidates should be confident; able to work under pressure and have the ability to communicate with staff at all levels throughout the organisation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It is important that applicants are able to demonstrate strong interpersonal and communication skills. The knowledge of a dental software package would be an advantage but not essential as full training will be given.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants should be flexible and willing to travel if required to other Dental Access Centre in Herefordshire.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
